      <div class="msgContentFrame">Hey Geldon, <br /> <br />excellent question. <br />The way I understand the implications of the &quot;fatigue&quot; system is that you should really ask yourself how often you're going to be playing. Are you a casual gamer, or gonna be playing a lot? I only say this because you could really do any and all tradeskill for all sorts of reasons. Repairs done to weapons are armor, crafting items for yourself or to sell. It seems like there can be a lot involved, but it depends on the individual. <br /> <br />That being said, I haven't looked much into the repair system, but it seems like Carpentry would be nice to have since it's how you make/repair at least the Harpoon (thus I assume other spears as well). Armorer/Leatherworker would be great for repairing your own equipment, as well as Weaver for undergarments and hempen armor. <br /> <br />I have my character doing a combination of Blacksmithing, Leatherworking, Goldsmithing, and Carpentry, but I'm not really making any of it a priority. Eventually I'll try to work on bits of each one, since they give nice EXP for physical levels without the hassle of fighting/grinding mobs. <br /> <br />There's also the role-playing aspect to consider, if you're into that. What does your character want to do? <br /> <br />Hope that helps!<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>FFXIV: Laurana Drakoid | Lancer | Alchemist | Rabanastre <br /><a href="http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=4245640" title="http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=4245640" rel="external nofollow">http://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=4245640</a></div></div>
